    "ai_response": "The paper presents a novel approach to enhance the DevNet model for fraud detection by incorporating a KNN-based similarity measure and a variational scaling factor. The key contributions include: (1) Using KNN to assign unlabeled samples to fraud or non-fraud clusters, (2) Calculating a similarity metric based on average distances to refine the deviation loss function, and (3) Demonstrating significant improvements in recall and block rate (approximately 6% and 1.3% respectively) compared to the baseline DevNet model. The method is applied to an internal dataset of refund claims with ~20% contamination, and the results highlight the importance of carefully calibrating the KNN parameter k to avoid noisy cluster assignments. The approach is scalable and has substantial operational impact at the company's scale."
