{
  "ai_response": {
    "ai_response": "The foundation model is designed to handle the complexity of a superapp ecosystem by leveraging unsupervised pre-training on diverse data modalities. This approach allows the model to learn a universal representation of the entire Grab ecosystem, capturing the intricate relationships between users, merchants, and drivers across all verticals. By combining masked language modeling with next action prediction, the model can predict not only the next item a user might choose but also the type of interaction they will engage in, enabling a more holistic understanding of user behavior and context.",
    "ai_response_2": "The model's architecture, built on a transformer framework, is specifically designed to address the challenges of joint pre-training on tabular and time-series data, handling a wide variety of data modalities, generalizing beyond a single task, and scaling to massive entity vocabularies. The use of adapter-based designs allows for flexibility and scalability, enabling the model to incorporate new modalities and adapt to future advancements in machine learning."
  },
