  "ai": {
    "ai": "The article discusses the development and implementation of an item matching system at Coupang, focusing on improving recall for identifying duplicate items in large product catalogs. The system leverages both text and image embeddings using FAISS for efficient similarity search and retrieval. The approach is compared against a traditional vector space model using Elasticsearch (ES), with the results showing significant improvements in recall, particularly in categories like beauty and food. The system is designed to run in parallel with the ES baseline, combining the strengths of both models to enhance accuracy. Future plans include incorporating additional item attributes and expanding the system to other areas such as visual similarity analysis and price comparison. The technical content reflects the company's research activities but does not necessarily indicate actual investment or product development plans."
  },
