    "response_content": "The article describes how the Fishbowl team used embedding methods to generate post recommendations in the absence of labeled data. They trained a content model using Doc2Vec and also explored a graph-based approach using BFS traversal to generate embeddings for users and posts. The hybrid model combining content and graph embeddings was deployed via MLFlow as a REST API service. The system ranks candidate posts for each user based on cosine similarity between user and post embeddings, serving the top-ranked posts in real-time. The inference process takes about 9 ms per batch request. The team also discusses limitations of the graph-based approach for dynamic data and plans to improve the model using transfer learning and additional features."
  },
