{
  "ai_response": "The new system is a contextual multi-armed bandit (CMAB) system, which allows for both exploration and exploitation of keyword bidding opportunities. The system is composed of three main components: a bid-to-spend model, a spend-to-return model, and a budget optimizer. The bid-to-spend model predicts the amount of spend based on the bid amount for each keyword. The spend-to-return model predicts the return on investment for different levels of spend. The budget optimizer ensures that the system stays within the allocated budget while maximizing returns. The system uses survival analysis and a non-parametric expectation-maximization algorithm to estimate the probability of winning a bid and the expected spend for each keyword. The system also uses a Hill function to model the relationship between spend and return for each keyword. The system uses Thompson sampling to introduce variety in the bidding strategy and avoid fixation on specific keywords.",
  "ai_response_length": 256
}

